21 February 2011Following the State of the Nation Address of 10 February 2011, Government will hold Cluster Media Briefings on the implementation of the Programme of Action 2011. The briefings will take place at Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape Town. There will be a video link-up to Room 153, Union Buildings, Pretoria. The last two media briefings are scheduled to take place as follows: Tuesday, 22 February 2011 11h00-12h30: International Cooperation, Trade &amp; Security Chairperson: Minister of Defence and Military Veterans, Lindiwe Sisulu Thursday, 24 February 2011 09h00-10h30: Economic Sectors and Employment Chairperson: Minister of Rural Development and Land Affairs, Gugile Nkwinti RSVP with: David Masango Cell: 083 279 7520 (Pretoria) Liezil Cerf Cell: 076 778 2380 (Cape Town) Enquiries: Neo Momodu Cell: 079 462 5081 Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)